      <byline class="print_byline">By P. J. Anthony</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Anthony, P J</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>India will phase out production of ozone-depleting substances like chlorofluorocarbons over 10 years with ehlp of $82 million grant administered through World Bank; grant is part of international agreement intended to preserve earth's ozone layer (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>India will phase out production of ozone-depleting substances like chlorofluorocarbons over 10 years with the help of an $82 million grant administered through the World Bank. The grant is part of an international agreement intended to preserve the earth's ozone layer. Chlorofluorocarbons were once widely used as refrigerants and propellants in aerosol products. India is the second-largest producer of them, after China.</p>
        <p>P. J. Anthony</p>
      </block>
